      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a legal principle that has been used to expand civil rights and personal liberties. It allows courts to protect individual rights that aren't explicitly mentioned in the Constitution, such as the right to privacy, which has been crucial in landmark cases like Roe v. Wade. This principle ensures that the government cannot infringe upon fundamental rights, even if they aren't specifically listed in the Constitution, thus promoting a broader understanding of liberty and justice.",
